Te in this stanza has a different reference to te in the next, and indeed to te all through the poem, which is addressed to Antonius. 54. solvet. The terms used in reference to the making and pay- ing of vows were, it may be said, borrowed from the courts of law. When the object for which the vow was made had been attained, the person making it was voti reus or voti damnatus, when he performed the vow he was solutus.
